00:31:43.732 --> 00:31:54.394
I give hints along the way, but I'm never there to wave it in your face and say this is what it is or isn't because I'm not here to financially advise you.

00:31:54.395 --> 00:32:04.923
That's not my job. I tell you to pray for things, and if you feel led to pray for it, fine—from gold to silver to all kinds of things.

00:32:04.924 --> 00:32:09.084
I said to pray about these things; I'm never here to tell you what to do.

00:32:09.085 --> 00:32:22.354
I even told you the day I said I bought silver—what was it, Braden?—back when it was less than $12 an ounce.

00:32:22.355 --> 00:32:48.879
It was a long time ago, and the Lord said, 'Today is a great day.'Then I told you recently, when it was at a hundred and some dollars, that the Lord said—after it was over, because I'm not a financial advisor—'Today is a great day to sell.'I said, 'Well, today is?'He said, 'Yes, today is a great day to sell.'So you follow the voice of the Lord and let the elevator go to the top.

00:32:48.880 --> 00:32:59.310
If you practice His presence, He'll lead you. If you don't want to practice His presence, you're wasting your time watching me because I'm all about Jesus.

00:32:59.311 --> 00:33:05.812
But I'm all about the end times. Ever since He said that, it's been hovering around way down here.

00:33:05.813 --> 00:33:20.185
When He says buy, you buy. When He says sell, sell. When He says hover, hover. Whatever He says to do, do it.

00:33:20.186 --> 00:33:33.265
He'll talk to me about certain things, and I listen to Him and I just go, 'Wow, okay.'It's the same about sports.

00:33:33.266 --> 00:33:44.298
People ask me, 'Brandon, who do you see in the NBA finals?'You want me to tell you who that was?

00:33:44.299 --> 00:33:53.808
Why? Because then you go out and gamble. 'Hey, tell me so I can put some money on it.'God doesn't do that.

00:33:53.809 --> 00:34:00.459
He's not going to talk about things if you have a gambling addiction and you go out and start betting on games.

00:34:00.460 --> 00:34:05.813
He tells you things if you're able to handle it and are mature.

00:34:05.814 --> 00:34:09.328
People go, 'Well, why not, Brandon?'Well, because God doesn't do that.

00:34:09.329 --> 00:34:13.779
That's not the way He works. People start gambling money and doing dumb things.

00:34:13.780 --> 00:34:20.398
But if you practice His presence, He'll tell you His heart, and we can just talk about things.

00:34:20.399 --> 00:34:28.719
Do you know how much Jesus loves you? He'll talk to you about the flowers, how to make them grow better.

00:34:28.720 --> 00:34:33.260
He'll talk to you about the seeds—when to plant something if there's going to be another frost.

00:34:33.261 --> 00:34:38.158
He'll say, 'Don't plant that yet. Don't go get flowers yet.'Why?

00:34:38.159 --> 00:34:44.603
Well, there's a frost coming on this date, and I'll write it down. Private things between me, my kids, and my wife.

00:34:44.604 --> 00:34:54.636
He'll say, 'There's a frost coming in two weeks.'Sure enough, it happens. It would kill my flowers because He knows I love flowers.

00:34:54.637 --> 00:34:58.969
Or He'll say, 'Hey, there's a storm coming in the next couple of—'and He'll give me the day.

00:34:58.970 --> 00:35:10.430
He'll say, 'There's going to be a storm coming here and you need to pray or pray over your area; there's a drought, you need to pray for more rain.'He'll talk to you about things that you're interested in.

00:35:10.431 --> 00:35:21.696
You know, when He says, 'I'll give you the desires,'He gives you the desires of your heart.

00:35:21.697 --> 00:35:27.034
People ask me, 'Brandon, do you see these angels? What are they doing?

00:35:27.035 --> 00:35:36.078
Do you talk to angels?'No, I don't talk to angels. I commission them.

00:35:36.079 --> 00:35:44.152
I tell them to go. I say, 'Lord, this is what You told me to do. And I know You give the angels to keep charge over me and to bear me up.

00:35:44.153 --> 00:35:48.719
But Father, I thank You that the angels are protecting my family.

00:35:48.720 --> 00:36:04.797
I thank You, Lord, that Your angels—I call prosperity angels to go out right now and get my money; cause it to come forth in Jesus'name.'What do you mean by that, Brandon? Demonic spirits are trying to hinder your blessing.

00:36:04.798 --> 00:36:26.319
If there was a principality hindering Daniel's blessing in the Old Covenant, and he had to fast for 21 days—he went before the Lord and started fasting with the Daniel fast—he had to have Michael come and help him.

00:36:26.320 --> 00:36:47.358
If there were angels that had to work an assignment to help Daniel with Michael—and when big bad Michael came up there with whatever he was doing, he went up there and did whatever he had to do to get the Prince of Persia off so he could get the answer.

00:36:47.359 --> 00:36:57.039
It's the same thing. The angels go because we wrestle not against flesh and blood.

00:36:57.040 --> 00:37:00.829
So people get all bent out of shape about whether we wrestle not against flesh.

00:37:00.830 --> 00:37:09.949
If we're not wrestling against the people who are persecuting us, it's the demons manifesting through them.

00:37:09.950 --> 00:37:17.590
Some of these people are just flat-out witches and warlocks, and they're assigned to try to kill, steal, and destroy with the devil.

00:37:17.591 --> 00:37:23.118
Just like I told you, the devil came and visited; he said these are witches.

00:37:23.119 --> 00:37:27.559
So you deal with all kinds of stuff like that, especially on platforms like this.

00:37:27.560 --> 00:37:34.765
You just plead the blood, take communion, and use your authority, but you're not dealing with the flesh. That's why those angels are sent.

00:37:34.766 --> 00:37:47.358
When I say, 'Go, ministering spirits, and help me bring forth the harvest,'it's because there are demonic spirits hindering your blessing.

00:37:47.359 --> 00:37:54.559
But I've said this before: you cannot draw from a well that is empty.

00:37:54.560 --> 00:38:05.390
The Bible says 30, 60, and 100-fold. You have to look in—you have a bank account, right?

00:38:05.391 --> 00:38:16.895
You go and look at your bank account and say, 'I need a readout of my account from the bank lady.'So I go to the bank lady and she says, 'This is what you have in your account.'You go, 'Oh, well, I have enough money.

00:38:16.896 --> 00:38:29.043
I can buy whatever I need; I can go to Walmart and buy my groceries.'You know what's in your account, but if you overspend, you're overdrawn and they're going to charge you thirty bucks.

00:38:29.044 --> 00:38:38.879
They overdraft because you overspent. That's the way it is in the spirit realm.

00:38:38.880 --> 00:38:48.382
What do you mean, Brandon? Everything is multiplied by seedtime and harvest. Whatsoever a man sows, that will he also reap.

00:38:48.383 --> 00:38:54.831
Good measure, pressed down, shaken together, and running over will men give unto your bosom.

00:38:54.832 --> 00:39:00.952
How? By your heavenly account. So I always look at the seeds I've sowed.

00:39:00.953 --> 00:39:04.360
The seeds you've sowed in the past will come to harvest at last.

00:39:04.361 --> 00:39:10.312
People go, 'What are you talking about?'It's when you give tithes and offerings to your church where you're getting fed.

00:39:10.313 --> 00:39:16.540
Bring your tithes to the storehouse. 'Well, I don't believe in tithing.'Well, then stay broke; I don't care what you think.

00:39:16.541 --> 00:39:22.399
I believe in tithing. I believe in giving. Give, and it shall be given unto you.

00:39:22.400 --> 00:39:26.148
People get mad about that. I don't care what you think. If you want to stay that way, fine.

00:39:26.149 --> 00:39:38.826
I know the system; I know how it works because I work it. And if you work God's system, it will work for you. So don't get mad. You sow.

00:39:38.827 --> 00:39:46.788
You look if it's multiplied by a hundredfold, thirty, sixty, or a hundredfold; you look at what's in that account, just like you do your bank balance.

00:39:46.789 --> 00:39:57.919
And you say, 'Well, if I gave $10, I've got a hundredfold return.'If it's good ground—if it's not, I just got 30—it's multiplied by 30, 60, and 100-fold.

00:39:57.920 --> 00:40:05.526
So, I look at what's in the account and I say, "At the bare minimum, Diana, we have this amount because we gave this in the church offering.

00:40:05.527 --> 00:40:11.913
We gave this to help the youth building. We sowed out of our ministry money.

00:40:11.914 --> 00:40:25.714
We're giving to a Red Zone for the church youth program."And I'm determined that this ministry is going to help pay that thing off because we don't want to have debt for the end times.

00:40:25.715 --> 00:40:32.593
And there's a massive youth building that we're trying to build right now in Collinsville, Oklahoma, that needs to be built right now.

00:40:32.594 --> 00:40:39.519
And so our ministry has given a lot into that to help for the youth harvest.

00:40:39.520 --> 00:40:48.335
I saw it's right across the street from the property that the church bought there, Pastor Chip and Candace.

00:40:48.336 --> 00:41:01.913
And it's a football field and all the kids go and on football nights celebrate and have parties after the Collinsville Cardinals play, right?

00:41:01.914 --> 00:41:15.199
So the Cardinals go over there and all the kids, because it's a small town, go out and get high and have sex and do things that they shouldn't be doing.

00:41:15.200 --> 00:41:24.273
And so, you know, weed's big in Oklahoma because everyone has medical—they don't have recreational, but it's medical—but you can get your license for nothing.

00:41:24.274 --> 00:41:29.351
So, people are smoking dope all the time now. So, the kids go out and get dope.

00:41:29.352 --> 00:41:50.531
So, we have a place across the street, directly across the street from the stadium, where we want to build a beautiful facility to have free pizza, free Cokes, and free all this stuff to bring those kids in and teach the people about Jesus and love on them.

00:41:50.532 --> 00:42:00.318
So, that's what they're doing right now. And every single time these kids, instead of going out and partying at these big houses, they're coming across the street and getting free food.

00:42:00.319 --> 00:42:05.096
So, we don't have room enough to receive all these kids. There's several hundred kids coming.

00:42:05.097 --> 00:42:24.318
So, our heart at our church where we are at, we said, "We've got to build a bigger youth place,"because I saw in the spirit a young man that will get saved that's a football player and he will go to a major college and he's going to bring revival to that college.

00:42:24.319 --> 00:42:47.439
And the Lord said, "Build this place across the street from this stadium so that this young man will come and give his heart to me, and the greatest harvest of souls will come from this young man, and I will use him to bring revival to a major college in the days ahead."He's going to be a star for football.

00:42:47.440 --> 00:42:52.559
So the Lord always speaks to you ahead. So that's what our heart is right now.

00:42:52.560 --> 00:42:58.763
So what is in my heavenly account? You can draw and ask the angels.

00:42:58.764 --> 00:43:05.235
You can't draw from a well that is empty—30, 60, 100-fold. That's what I'm trying to tell y'all.

00:43:05.236 --> 00:43:11.439
When you give, you give in the purpose. You sow a seed to reap a harvest.

00:43:11.440 --> 00:43:18.588
You give into good ground to bring in the youth. Did you show them the building, the football stadium?

00:43:18.589 --> 00:43:28.633
Could you show them the Red Zone? Show them that. I get excited about stuff like this.

00:43:28.634 --> 00:43:39.125
That's where my heart is. My heart is the harvest. And this is it: Collinsville, Oklahoma. That's it right here. Show them a picture of it.

00:43:39.126 --> 00:43:47.905
I don't know if they'd mind that because it's kids, but you can show them a picture of the kids all going right there in the big picture.

00:43:47.906 --> 00:44:03.065
That's fine. No, go down right there. Show them. Give them a sneak peek. That's what I'm talking about.

00:44:03.066 --> 00:44:14.959
So they're coming in and the youth groups are coming in and we want to make a massive facility for all these high school kids coming across the street, and they're not going out and sleeping around and doing what they're doing anymore.

00:44:14.960 --> 00:44:18.160
But you give into stuff like that. That's what I'm trying to tell you.

00:44:18.161 --> 00:44:22.357
So when you've given to me, and this is where I sow my money, this is why I'm trying to help.

00:44:22.358 --> 00:44:32.633
And I told Diana, I said, "This is my heart: a harvest."But people want to know 30, 60, 100-fold return when you call for the angels to help you.

00:44:32.635 --> 00:44:38.235
You can't draw from a well that is dry. It's by multiplication.

00:44:38.236 --> 00:44:42.879
But you've got to look at your heavenly account. Keep track of your seeds.

00:44:42.880 --> 00:44:50.953
Keep track of how much you've given to the church. And you say, "Well, I just pluck it."I don't just dump it and pluck it.

00:44:50.954 --> 00:45:06.479
You know, like, "Well, you just let it hit the bucket—change."I am strategic in everything I do when God tells me to do something and I say I'm going to write it down.

00:45:06.480 --> 00:45:13.679
So this is what's in my heavenly account. So I have a legal right in the spirit realm to call that forth.

00:45:13.680 --> 00:45:23.855
You cannot call forth $100,000 if you don't have a hundred thousand multiplied seed in there.

00:45:23.856 --> 00:45:29.979
It's spiritual law. But people want to get all flaky and they go, "Well, it's over here.

00:45:29.980 --> 00:45:36.277
I believe in God for $10 million, brother."And I'm like, "But do you have $10 million of the seed in the ground?

00:45:36.278 --> 00:45:43.437
Because if you don't, you might as well say Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Star because you aren't going to receive it.

00:45:43.438 --> 00:45:46.834
I don't care what you're saying. The seed always multiplies.

00:45:46.835 --> 00:45:51.192
A seed always produces after its own kind, but it always comes back in multiplication.

00:45:51.193 --> 00:46:10.719
If a farmer planted one row of corn and said, "I'm believing for this whole field to come in, brother,"and we're out there going, "Oh,"and you're out there praying over the seed, but you only planted one row, but I believe for the whole field, you're crazy.

00:46:10.720 --> 00:46:20.799
It's not going to happen. I don't care how much you pray. If the seed isn't in the ground, you're not going to reap it.

00:46:20.800 --> 00:46:33.199
And you can only call by spiritual law and asking the angels and the Lord to help you by what you have sown into the local church, to your ministry where you are.

00:46:33.200 --> 00:46:40.078
Help your pastor. Help your congregation. Where do you go to church?

00:46:40.079 --> 00:46:45.837
And if you say, "Well, I don't want to give there,"then why are you going to church there?

00:46:45.838 --> 00:46:59.838
That's dumb. Go to a place where you get fed. And when you get fed by the Word of God there, help that ministry out. Even if it's just $10, help them.

00:46:59.839 --> 00:47:10.417
If you sit in their pew and go to the bathroom and flush their toilet or whatever, use their toilet paper and use their soap on your hands.

00:47:10.418 --> 00:47:14.479
Use your faith to believe God with them. There's Pastor Chip right here.

00:47:14.480 --> 00:47:20.196
You want to show him, Pastor Chip? He's the one in the black hat.

00:47:20.197 --> 00:47:28.554
He goes down there and ministers to these kids and he's eating a snow cone.

00:47:28.555 --> 00:47:34.231
Show them the Red Zone. That's where my heart's at: the youth of this nation.

00:47:34.233 --> 00:47:44.858
The Lord told me, "Satan came after the youth hard and I'm coming after them harder."And we're going to bring in the greatest harvest of souls this world has ever seen before.

00:47:44.859 --> 00:47:47.067
And it's all going to start in a place like Collinsville, Oklahoma.

00:47:47.068 --> 00:47:52.049
It's going to start in places like this that are small, that are just across the street from a stadium.

00:47:52.050 --> 00:47:56.632
And you can see the flag in the background. That's the stadium. That's how close the Red Zone is.

00:47:56.633 --> 00:48:07.495
We put the cones out there so that the kids are safe, but the stadium's right across the street.

00:48:07.496 --> 00:48:13.598
They come across the street. That's how close it is. So just believe in God.

00:48:13.599 --> 00:48:24.536
I'm trying to show you things to get excited, but I want you to be motivated in your ministries, what God has called you to do in your area.

00:48:24.537 --> 00:48:35.199
It's all hands on deck right now. And if you're not doing something to bring in the harvest, if you're not doing something in your local community, why aren't you?

00:48:35.200 --> 00:48:50.190
If you live in a small town or a big city, help your church; help them bring in the harvest. I talked to a mega-minister today and we were talking.

00:48:50.191 --> 00:48:59.519
I said, "The Lord told me,"and he said, "Brandon, what are we looking for?"I said, "This is what I'm believing for."He said, "I'm not—you're not waiting on me.

00:48:59.520 --> 00:49:07.856
I'm waiting on you. You bring in my harvest, I'll come and get you."Jesus said that to me, 'Brandon, I'm waiting on the fruit.

00:49:07.857 --> 00:49:17.456
I have long patience for the fruit, but time is running out. What are you going to do to help me bring in this harvest?

00:49:17.457 --> 00:49:24.842
For the harvest is plentiful and the laborers are few.'There are billions dying and going to hell. What will you do?

00:49:24.843 --> 00:49:33.095
Are we just going to sit back and pray and have these little prayer services and just sit there and go, 'Well, Jesus, get them all saved'?

00:49:33.096 --> 00:49:44.879
He is waiting on us. Get a fire shut up in your bones. And no, that's why I said, 'Lord, I'm tired of hearing about Smith Wigglesworth.

00:49:44.880 --> 00:49:54.327
I'm tired of hearing about Kathryn Kuhlman. I'm tired of hearing about Rachel Teafatiller and all these prayer generals and the people of the past.

00:49:54.328 --> 00:49:59.358
I don't want to hear about it anymore. What about my generation?

00:49:59.359 --> 00:50:07.199
What about the people behind this camera right now? What about your church? What about the churches in Chicago?

00:50:07.200 --> 00:50:23.705
What about the churches in Philadelphia, New York City, Miami, and Atlanta, and all these other places that need a touch from Jesus and they're desperate?'I know God stationed me in a little place to go to church over here and visit.

00:50:23.706 --> 00:50:37.596
And he said, 'Go back there and help them. Pray for them.'And I saw the youth coming in by the hundreds—not thousands because there are not thousands there—by the hundreds.

00:50:37.597 --> 00:50:48.159
But it takes one person; one person led Billy Graham to Jesus, and Billy Graham led millions.

00:50:48.160 --> 00:51:00.399
Who was the person that led my friends to Jesus? I must mess up his name again: Maldonado.

00:51:00.400 --> 00:51:10.795
Maldonado has led millions to Jesus. He talks about him. Maldonado is going to Brazil in a couple weeks.

00:51:10.796 --> 00:51:27.679
And who led him to Jesus? But it took one spark to spread a major fire. It takes one person to reach millions.

00:51:27.680 --> 00:51:37.338
And he says, 'I have somebody here.'So whatever your vision is, do it with all your heart. Don't do it halfway.

00:51:37.339 --> 00:51:59.679
It's like I told Pastor Chip, I said, 'We've got to make the greatest facility with what God has given us so that everybody in Oklahoma, Tulsa, and all these areas talk about how great the Collinsville, Oklahoma youth group is.'They are in a place with a population of hardly anybody; it has probably two stoplights.

00:51:59.680 --> 00:52:08.542
But why not do it and do it well? Why should we get the hand-me-downs in church and people go, 'Well, you know, it's just the youth'?

00:52:08.543 --> 00:52:18.159
No, it's the next generation. It's the next generation. For you were once a youth and so was I.

00:52:18.160 --> 00:52:30.265
So, that's why I try to tell you all a little bit more about me, but I don't know if you even wanted to hear that tonight, but people want to know about this kind of stuff I'm talking about.

00:52:30.266 --> 00:52:41.358
And I say it by the unction of the Holy Spirit. Be bold about what God's called you to do in these last days, but do it with all your heart.

00:52:41.359 --> 00:52:50.959
Get a backbone like a crowbar, get enthusiastic about it, and get some passion.

00:52:50.960 --> 00:52:56.765
Don't say, 'Well, it's just somebody else's responsibility.'When Jesus told me, he said, 'It's all hands on deck.

00:52:56.766 --> 00:53:02.497
Brandon, will you help me bring in the harvest?'I saw his hands, and Jesus was in the field.

00:53:02.498 --> 00:53:07.260
He was in overalls and he had a piece of wheat in his mouth and he put it up here.

00:53:07.261 --> 00:53:16.197
I saw the wheat bowing down and I saw harvest equipment, and the barn was full of the glory and the anointing.

00:53:16.198 --> 00:53:25.697
And he said, 'Do you see the angel armies that are coming? I've released the host of heaven to help you, for you're not alone.

00:53:25.698 --> 00:53:37.584
For there are more with you than there are with them.'You're not doing this alone, ladies and gentlemen, for there's more with you than there are with them.

00:53:37.585 --> 00:53:44.535
And I saw the angels and the host of heaven coming out, and they looked like a waterfall coming on this earth.

00:53:44.536 --> 00:53:50.803
And there were two angels per one unsaved person, and they were lined up.

00:53:50.804 --> 00:53:55.897
And he said, 'I'm giving you a window of uninterrupted and unhindered.

00:53:55.898 --> 00:54:12.479
For Satan has blinded the eyes of the unbeliever, and I'm calling in the unsaved, for I've come to save that which was lost.'The harvest equipment is the anointing.

00:54:12.480 --> 00:54:18.461
And I saw Jesus walking amongst the wheat, and he was rubbing his hands all in it.

00:54:18.462 --> 00:54:29.679
And as I could see his hands rubbing through that wheat, he had massive holes in his hands, massive holes.

00:54:29.680 --> 00:54:33.759
And I could see through his hands. And I could see the wheat through his hands.

00:54:33.760 --> 00:54:38.630
And he said, 'Brandon, I suffered for every single one of them.

00:54:38.631 --> 00:54:45.759
I suffered for every single one of them. Help me bring in the harvest.

00:54:45.760 --> 00:54:53.816
Help me bring in the harvest. The harvest is plentiful and the laborers are few.

00:54:53.817 --> 00:55:03.485
Help me bring in the harvest.'I looked at him and I said, 'I'll do my best. As for me and my house, Lord, we will serve you.

00:55:03.486 --> 00:55:10.239
We will do whatever it takes to help bring in the harvest.'He said, 'I know you will.

00:55:10.240 --> 00:55:24.078
I know you will.'I'm just trying to tell you tonight there's so many things we can get stuck on.

00:55:24.079 --> 00:55:37.971
There's so many problems we have in our lives—the storms of life, the cares of this world that choke out everything and keep us distracted from what this person's saying or that person, and people persecute you for the word's sake. But it doesn't matter.

00:55:37.972 --> 00:55:57.336
All I know is when I stand before my Father, he'll judge me by what I've done for him and he'll look at me and say, 'Well done, thy good and faithful servant.'Or, 'Well, you could have done better.'But I don't want to stand before him and say, 'Hey, at least I tried.'I tried.

00:55:57.338 --> 00:56:03.580
